âœ… QUESTION 3: LRU CACHE

ğŸ“Œ Asked in: Amazon, Google, Microsoft, Meta
ğŸ“Œ Concepts: HashMap + Doubly Linked List, Design
ğŸ“Œ Difficulty: Hard (but very standard)

ğŸ” PROBLEM STATEMENT

Design a data structure that supports the following operations in O(1) time:

get(key) â†’ Returns the value of the key if present, else -1

put(key, value) â†’ Inserts or updates the value.

If the cache reaches capacity, remove the Least Recently Used (LRU) item before inserting the new one.

LRU (Least Recently Used):
The key that was used least recently should be evicted first.

ğŸ§ª Example
LRUCache cache = new LRUCache(2);

cache.put(1, 1);  // cache = {1=1}
cache.put(2, 2);  // cache = {1=1, 2=2}
cache.get(1);     // returns 1 â†’ cache = {2=2, 1=1}
cache.put(3, 3);  // evicts key 2 â†’ cache = {1=1, 3=3}
cache.get(2);     // returns -1 (not found)
cache.put(4,4);   // evicts key 1 â†’ cache = {3=3, 4=4}
cache.get(1);     // returns -1
cache.get(3);     // returns 3
cache.get(4);     // returns 4

ğŸ§  CORE IDEA (INTERVIEW INSIGHT)

We need O(1) get & put â†’ two data structures combined:

HashMap<Key, Node> â†’ For O(1) access to nodes

Doubly Linked List â†’ For O(1) removal/insertion of nodes

Front of DLL â†’ Most recently used

End of DLL â†’ Least recently used

ğŸ› ï¸ ALGORITHM (STEP BY STEP)
â–¶ get(key)

If key exists â†’ move node to front of DLL â†’ return value

Else â†’ return -1

â–¶ put(key, value)

If key exists â†’ update value + move to front

Else

If capacity reached â†’ remove tail node (LRU)

Insert new node at front

â±ï¸ COMPLEXITY
Operation	Time	Space
get	O(1)	O(n)
put	O(1)	O(n)
ğŸ’» JAVA CODE (INTERVIEW-READY)
import java.util.*;

class LRUCache {

    class Node {
        int key, val;
        Node prev, next;
        Node(int key, int val) { this.key = key; this.val = val; }
    }

    private int capacity;
    private Map<Integer, Node> map;
    private Node head, tail;

    public LRUCache(int capacity) {
        this.capacity = capacity;
        map = new HashMap<>();
        
        // dummy nodes to simplify insert/remove
        head = new Node(0,0);
        tail = new Node(0,0);
        head.next = tail;
        tail.prev = head;
    }

    private void remove(Node node) {
        node.prev.next = node.next;
        node.next.prev = node.prev;
    }

    private void addToFront(Node node) {
        node.next = head.next;
        node.prev = head;
        head.next.prev = node;
        head.next = node;
    }

    public int get(int key) {
        if (!map.containsKey(key)) return -1;
        Node node = map.get(key);
        remove(node);
        addToFront(node);
        return node.val;
    }

    public void put(int key, int value) {
        if (map.containsKey(key)) {
            Node node = map.get(key);
            node.val = value;
            remove(node);
            addToFront(node);
        } else {
            if (map.size() == capacity) {
                Node lru = tail.prev;
                remove(lru);
                map.remove(lru.key);
            }
            Node newNode = new Node(key, value);
            addToFront(newNode);
            map.put(key, newNode);
        }
    }
}

ğŸ§¾ LINE-BY-LINE EXPLANATION
ğŸ”¹ Node class
class Node { int key, val; Node prev, next; }


â¡ï¸ Stores key & value, with links for DLL

ğŸ”¹ Dummy head & tail
head = new Node(0,0); tail = new Node(0,0);
head.next = tail; tail.prev = head;


â¡ï¸ Simplifies edge cases for insert/remove

ğŸ”¹ remove(node)
node.prev.next = node.next;
node.next.prev = node.prev;


â¡ï¸ Remove a node from DLL in O(1)

ğŸ”¹ addToFront(node)
node.next = head.next;
node.prev = head;
head.next.prev = node;
head.next = node;


â¡ï¸ Inserts node at front (MRU)

ğŸ”¹ get(key)
Node node = map.get(key);
remove(node);
addToFront(node);
return node.val;


â¡ï¸ Access node â†’ move to front â†’ return value

ğŸ”¹ put(key, value)

If exists â†’ update + move to front

Else if full â†’ remove LRU (tail.prev)

Add new node to front + map

ğŸ§ª DRY RUN EXAMPLE
cache = LRUCache(2)
put(1,1) â†’ cache = {1=1}
put(2,2) â†’ cache = {1=1, 2=2}
get(1)   â†’ returns 1, cache order = {2=2, 1=1}
put(3,3) â†’ evict 2, cache = {1=1, 3=3}
get(2)   â†’ -1


âœ” Works perfectly in O(1) time

